    <p><strong>Start here:</strong> use <strong>15g coffee</strong>, <strong>240g water</strong>, a <strong>medium-fine grind</strong>, and water around <strong>185 to 195°F</strong>. Let the coffee steep for about <strong>75 to 90 seconds total</strong>, then press slowly for another <strong>20 to 30 seconds</strong>. That is the easiest AeroPress timing for a cup that tastes sweet, balanced, and clean.</p>
    <p>Think of it like cooking pasta al dente. Too short and it feels underdone. Too long and everything gets mushy. AeroPress timing works the same way. You are looking for that middle zone where the cup still has sparkle, but it also has enough body to feel finished.</p>

